# Safety net for automatic-updates.py.
#
# List a release tag (e.g. 0.0.0.8) or a dev-branch commit SHA (short or
# full, e.g. 83937c3) on its own line to stop every device's
# automatic-updates plugin from auto-installing that specific version,
# starting from the very next check any device makes -- no new release
# or device-side code change needed.
#
# This file is always fetched fresh from the main branch's current HEAD,
# separately from whatever release/commit is actually being considered
# for install. That means it works retroactively: even a version that's
# already published and already tagged bad can be blocked after the
# fact just by adding a line here and pushing to main.
#
# A blocked version still shows as "update available" on the device --
# it just won't be auto-installed. Whoever's running that device needs
# to update it manually (SSH in, or reflash).
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
